### CHAPTER XXXIII.

*Hûspâram Nask*.

1\. One section is about the mode and object *of* confinement as regards
a beast *of burden*, sheep, and dog that are mad (dêvânakŏ), and the
operation of the affliction (vakhsi*s*nŏ); also to what extent is their
restoration; *and* when not restored, *but* come for slaughter, the care
of them even in confinement,

<span id="page_106">p. 106</span>

*and* whatever is on the same subject. 2. About the harm (vinâs) which
the beast *of burden*, sheep, *and* dog shall commit. 3. About the sin
which killed *one who is* no offender <span
id="fr_274"></span>[1](#fn_273.md). 4. About the care and remedy *for* a
sick dog, *and* whatever is on the same subject.

